      "side": 1,
      "message": "On 64 bit architectures FILTER_INDEX(base) could currently be \u003e FILTER_INDEX(base + size - 1) which would cause an out of bounds access. Better not to mask in FILTER_INDEX, but to mask in [SG]ET_FILTER_BIT.\n\nAlso: the breakpad code is written the way it was because it had to run in a compromised context. Because you don\u0027t have that restriction, you could use a binary search on a sorted array of ranges, and probably skip the bitmasking.",
